<body style="background-color:rgb(200, 235, 255);">
    <hr width="100%" color="black">
    <h3>Our climber lifts our robot on all positions of the bar. We use a pneumatic cylinder, a set of belts and pulleys, and three rotating arms to lift our hook to the height of the bar. We use a gearbox and winch to bring the hook down and cause the robot to climb.</h3>
    <hr width="100%" color="black">
    <h1>DESIGN REQUIREMENTS:</h1>
    <p>
        <ul style=“list-style-type:square”>

            <h3><li>Align for a climb within 7 seconds</li>
            
            <li>Complete the climb within 3 seconds</li>
            
            <li>Reach up to a bar of 73"</li>
            
            <li>Stowed Height under 27 inches</li>
            
            <li>Safely lift robot of 150 lbs 32″ off the ground</li>
            </ul></h3>
    </p>
    <hr width="100%" color="black">
    <h1>FINAL CAD DESIGN:</h1>
